py, all serotonergic agents should be discontinued immediately and supportive care rendered as necessary. Moderately ill patients may also benefit from the administration of a serotonin antagonist (e.g., cyproheptadine, chlorpromazine).', 'Synergism', 'The use of citalopram is not recommended in patients receiving other drugs that prolong the QT interval.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/67234/', '', 'Viloxazine, Trazodone', 'Citalopram, Esketamine', 1767369485);
